OL,3,CHouseholds urged to send in energy
OL,4,Cmeter readings ahead of October 1
OL,5,Cprice hike
OL,7,FAlmost 10 million households have been
OL,8,Fwarned they risk overpaying for their
OL,9,Fenergy if they do not send meter
OL,10,Freadings to their supplier before a
OL,11,F10% price rise takes effect on October
OL,12,F1.
OL,14,FThe average household energy bill is
OL,15,Fto increase by #149 a year from
OL,16,FTuesday as Ofgem increases its price
OL,17,Fcap just as homes move into the winter
OL,18,Fmonths.
