OL,3,CHouseholds urged to send in energy
OL,4,Cmeter readings ahead of October 1
OL,5,Cprice hike
OL,7,FSuppliers who have not received meter
OL,8,Freadings base their bills on estimated
OL,9,Fusage, meaning households could be
OL,10,Foverpaying, while others may not be
OL,11,Fpaying enough.
OL,13,FThe price cap sets a maximum price
OL,14,Fthat energy suppliers can charge
OL,15,Fconsumers for each kilowatt hour (kWh)
OL,16,Fof energy they use.
OL,18,FIt does not limit total bills because
OL,19,Fhouseholders still pay for the amount
OL,20,Fof energy they consume.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/11
