OL,5,Cprice hike
OL,7,FOctober's price cap will be
OL,8,Fsignificantly lower than during the
OL,9,Fpeak of the energy crisis, which was
OL,10,Ffuelled by Russia's invasion of
OL,11,FUkraine in February 2022, driving up
OL,12,Fcosts in an already-turbulent market.
OL,14,FHowever, experts think there is likely
OL,15,Fto be a further increase in January,
OL,16,Fwith more rises possible early in the
OL,17,Fnew year due to escalating tensions in
OL,18,Fthe Russia-Ukraine war.
