OL,4,Cmeter readings ahead of October 1
OL,5,Cprice hike
OL,7,FOfgem chief executive Jonathan
OL,8,FBrearley has urged consumers to "shop
OL,9,Faround" and consider a fixed-rate
OL,10,Ftariff that could save money, adding
OL,11,Fthat the regulator was working with
OL,12,FGovernment, suppliers, charities and
OL,13,Fconsumer groups to do "everything we
OL,14,Fcan" to support customers.
OL,16,FCitizens Advice has said it was
OL,17,Fparticularly concerned about
OL,18,Fhouseholds with children and young
OL,19,Fpeople and those on lower incomes, who
OL,20,Fwere most likely to struggle with
OL,21,Ftheir heating costs.
